Load a mesh from a file.

Load a mesh from a file. If entity set is specified, loaded mesh is added to that set; specify root set if that is not desired.

Parameters:
instance  [in] iMesh instance handle
entity_set_handle  [in] Set to which loaded mesh will be added, otherwise root
name  [in] File name from which mesh is to be loaded
options  [in] Pointer to implementation-specific options string (Option Strings)
err  [out] Returned Error status (see iBase_ErrorType)
name_len  [in] Length of the file name character string (String Length Arguments)
options_len  [in] Length of the options character string (String Length Arguments)

Save a mesh to a file.

Save a mesh to a file. If entity set is specified, save only the mesh contained in that set.

Parameters:
instance  [in] iMesh instance handle
entity_set_handle  [in] Entity set being saved

err  [out] Returned Error status (see iBase_ErrorType)

void iMesh_setGeometricDimension ( iMesh_Instance  instance,
int  geom_dim,
int *  err 
)

Set geometric dimension of vertex coordinates.

Set the geometric dimension of the mesh. Note: An application should not expect this function to succeed unless the mesh database is empty (no vertices created, no files read, etc.)

Precondition:
iMesh instance must be empty; no vertex entities
Parameters:
instance  [in] iMesh instance handle
geom_dim  [in] Requested geometric dimension.
err  [out] Returned Error status (see iBase_ErrorType)
